$ Linux kernel

The kernel is responsible for
  • memory management
  • taks scheduling
  • I/O
  • interprocess communication (IPO)
  • etc

The kernel itself is loaded as an image file: `zImage` or `→Linux/fhs/boot/bzImage[bzImage]`.

